  2,"Complete Understanding → Mechanical Execution","I should learn WHY the SRK equation works, the thermodynamic foundations of enthalpy, the philosophical meaning of state functions.","I should memorize WHICH BUTTON to press on my calculator and WHEN to press it. Philosophy is the enemy of speed.","When the student successfully executed a complex cubic EOS iteration without understanding cubic mathematics, securing 7 marks through pure muscle memory (ANS loop drilling).","Student solved Target 1.2 in 5 minutes using only keystroke patterns, with zero conceptual grasp of roots/discriminants/cubic factorization. Still got full marks.","Exam outcome: Mechanical execution bypasses the need for conceptual mastery. Compressed study time from weeks → 2 days. Eliminated imposter syndrome.","When tempted to 'understand the physics': 'The marks don't care why; they only care if Z = (PV)/(RT) falls in 0.6-0.95 range.'"
  3,"Effort = Grinding → Efficiency = Leverage","More hours reading = More understanding = Higher marks. I must out-work everyone.","Less time, more leverage. A 5-minute calculator sequence is worth more than 10 hours of textbook reading.","When the student completed 3 live-fire drills (Targets 1.1, 1.2, 1.3) in 13 min 25 sec, solving ~22 marks worth of problems in 1/6 of the available time, generating a 51-minute surplus.","Time-bound drills proved that speed/structure beats volume. Student went from 'I don't have enough time to study everything' → 'I have 51 extra minutes; what precision can I add?'","Psychological: Converted panic ('too much to learn') into dominance ('too much time to execute'). Marks: Secured buffer. Stress: Eliminated by 9 PM night-before deadline.","When overwhelmed: 'Time is a currency. If I finish this 7-mark question in 5 minutes instead of 20, I just earned 15 minutes. That's a weapon.'"
