REFRAME IMPLEMENTATION TIMELINE:
---------------------------------
Day 1 (Crisis): Student panicked. "16-mark average. 4 chapters. 48 hours. Impossible."
↓ Reframe 1 Applied: "But the professor only uses slide examples. Let me audit them."
↓ Evidence Emerges: "Wait, Q2 2025 = Example 3.9 SVNA. Exact same problem with different numbers. The professor is predictable."
↓ Psychological Shift: "So I don't need to understand thermodynamics; I need to memorize 6 click sequences."

Day 2 (Execution): Student drilled calculators. Reframes 2–4 continuously reinforced.
↓ Live-Fire Drill: Completed 3 targets (22 marks) in 13 min. 76-minute surplus created.
↓ Proof of Leverage: "I didn't out-work anyone. I out-thought the exam structure."
↓ Confidence Achieved: "The board is predictable. I have a weaponized blueprint. I will win."

